#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rcmapem Colormap Edit Menu #!N #!EC #!N #!N The 
Colormap  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF menu displays the options used to edit 
the current color map. #!N #!N The following options appear on 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF menu: #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Undo #!EF #!I50 #!N Returns an operation to its previous 
value.  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Undo #!EF retains a stack of 10 operations. #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Copy #!EF #!I50 #!N Copies selected control points 
to a buffer so that they can be pasted to another 
field. See  #!Lcapcps,dxall373 h Copying and Pasting Control Points  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Paste #!EF #!I50 
#!N Pastes selected control points to a different field. See  #!Lcapcps,dxall373 h Copying and Pasting Control Points  #!EL  
. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Use Application Default #!EF #!I50 #!N 
If the Colormap Editor is data-driven, it is still possible to 
override its data-driven values by explicitly setting them in the Colormap 
Editor. The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Use Application Default #!EF option restores the data-driven 
values. It generates a cascade menu with four suboptions: #!N #!I0 
#!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Color (HSV) Map #!EF #!EF 
#!I50 #!N If a color map was provided to the color-map 
tab of the Colormap tool, and was subsequently modified by the 
user (i.e, adding, moving, or deleting control points), selection of this 
suboption restores the original color map. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Opacity Map #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N If an opacity map was 
provided to the opacity tab of the Colormap tool, and was 
subsequently modified by the user (i.e, adding, moving, or deleting control 
points), selection of this suboption restores the original opacity map. #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Minimum #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N If the 
minimum was set either by a field passed to the data 
tab of the Colormap tool or by a value passed to 
or set for the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   min #!EF parameter of Colormap, and 
was subsequently modified by the user in the Colormap Editor, this 
suboption restores the original value. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Maximum 
#!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N If the maximum was set either by 
a field passed to the data tab of the Colormap tool 
or by a value passed to or set for the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
max #!EF parameter of Colormap, and was subsequently modified by the 
user in the Colormap Editor, this suboption restores the original value. 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   All #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N Restores 
all values to their data-driven settings. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Minimum & Maximum #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N Restores both the minimum 
and the maximum values of the original color map. #!I0 #!N 
#!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add Control Points... #!EF #!I50 #!N 
Brings up a dialog box in which you can enter the 
exact numerical location for control points to be added as the 
data value and as the value for either the Hue, Saturation, 
Value, or Opacity area of the color map. See  #!Ladconp,dxall367 h Adding Control Points  #!EL  . 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Constrain Horizontal #!EF #!I50 #!N Constrains the 
horizontal movement of all control points in all areas of the 
Colormap. See  #!Lmovcps,dxall371 h Moving Control Points  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Constrain Vertical #!EF 
#!I50 #!N Constrains the vertical movement of all control points in 
all areas of the color map. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Generate 
Waveforms #!EF #!I50 #!N Displays a dialog box that allows you 
to select from a menu of waveforms. The waveforms can be 
applied to the full range of hue, saturation, value or opacity 
or to a selected range. See  #!Lcrewvs,dxall372 h Creating Waveforms  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Delete Selected Control Points #!EF #!I50 #!N Deletes selected control 
points in the selected area of the Colormap. #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Select All Control Points #!EF #!I50 #!N Selects all the 
control points in the selected area of the Colormap. #!I0 #!N 
#!N #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N #!N  #!Lcmapxm,dxall467 h Colormap Execute Menu  #!EL  
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
